**3.-**

**3.a.-**

C++
``` c++
#include <iostream>
#include <vector>
using namespace std;


int longest(int cur, int t, vector<int>& visited, vector<int>& V, vector<pair<int,int>>& E) {
    if (cur == t)
        return 0;
    visited[cur] = 1;

    int longestPath = 0;
    for (int i=0; i<(int)E.size(); i++) {
        if (E[i].first==cur || E[i].second==cur) {
            int next = (E[i].first==cur) ? E[i].second : E[i].first;
            if (visited[next])
                continue;   // already visited, skip
            longestPath = max(longestPath, longest(next, t, visited, V, E));
        }
    }

    visited[cur] = 0; // backtrack
    return longestPath+1;
}


/* Example usage */
int main() {
    vector<int> V;
    vector<pair<int,int>> E;
    vector<int> visited;
    
    V = {0, 1, 2, 3, 4}; // Example vertices
    E = {{0, 1}, {1, 2}, {2, 3}, {3, 4}, {4, 0}}; // Example edges (directed graph)
    visited.resize(V.size(), 0);
    
    cout << longest(0, 4, visited, V, E) << endl;

    return 0;
}
```

Pseudo-code:
``` pseudo-code

visited = [false for every index, for the size of V]

longest(cur, t, visited, V, E)
    if cur == t then
        return 0
    
    visited[cur] = true

    longestPath = 0
    for every edge in E
        if edge.first == cur or edge.second == cur then
            next = the other vertex in the edge that is not cur
            if visited[next] then
                continue // already visited, skip
            longestPath = max(longestPath, longest(next, t, visited, V, E))
    
    visited[cur] = false // reset visited for backtracking
    return longestPath + 1
```


**3.b.-**

Neste caso nao se pode aplicar optimal structure, pois as soluções que podem ser optimas para subproblemas nao sao otimas para o problema "parent".

Exemplo:
A solução optima para S->t é S->a->b->c->d->t.

Partindo deste problema, vamos para o subproblema b->t, cuja solução otima é b->a->d->c->t, em vez de b->c->d->t, que é a solução otima para o problema "parent" S->t.

**4.a.-**

C++
``` c++
#include <iostream>
#include <vector>
#include <climits>
#include <algorithm>
using namespace std;

#define n 3

int p[n][n][n] = {
    {
        {5, 7, 13},
        {2, 8, 11},
        {6, 9, 14}
    },
    {
        {8,  6,  9},
        {4, 10, 12},
        {7, 15, 17}
    },
    {
        {3,  4,  12},
        {5,  16, 18},
        {13, 19, 21}
    }
};

vector<vector<int>> dp = vector<vector<int>>(n, vector<int>(n, -1));

int M(int i, int j) {
    if (i == j)
        return 0;

    if (dp[i][j] != -1)
        return dp[i][j];

    int minimum = INT_MAX;
    for (int k=i; k<j; k++) {
        minimum = min(minimum, M(i,k) + M(k+1,j) + p[i][k][j]);
    }

    dp[i][j] = minimum;
    return minimum;
}

// Example usage
int main() {
    cout << M(0, n-1) << endl;
    return 0;
}

```

Pseudo-code:
``` pseudo-code

dp = matrix of size n x n, initialized to -1

function M(i, j)
    if i = j then
        return 0

    if dp has value at [i][j] then
        return dp[i][j]

    minimum = infinity
    for k so that i <= k < j
        minimum = min(minimum, M(i, k) + M(k+1, j) + p[i,k,j])

    dp[i][j] = minimum
    return minimum

```


**4.b.-**


ATENCAO é necessário que i vá de n-1 até 0 em vez de, 0 até n como de costume, pois como podemos ver na chamada recursiva "M(k+1, j)", o valor de i depende de i+1, precisando de calcular os valores maiores primeiro. 

C++
``` c++
#include <iostream>
#include <vector>
#include <climits>
#include <algorithm>
using namespace std;

#define n 3

int p[n][n][n] = {
    {
        {5, 7, 13},
        {2, 8, 11},
        {6, 9, 14}
    },
    {
        {8,  6,  9},
        {4, 10, 12},
        {7, 15, 17}
    },
    {
        {3,  4,  12},
        {5,  16, 18},
        {13, 19, 21}
    }
};


int M(int a, int b) {
    vector<vector<int>> dp = vector<vector<int>>(n, vector<int>(n, -1));


    for (int i=n-1; i>=0; i--) {
        for (int j=i; j<n; j++) {

            if (i==j) {
                dp[i][j] = 0;
                continue;
            }
            
            dp[i][j] = INT_MAX;
            for (int k=i; k<j; k++) {
                dp[i][j] = min(dp[i][j], dp[i][k]+dp[k+1][j]+p[i][k][j]);
            }
        }
    }

    return dp[0][n-1];
}

// Example usage
int main() {
    cout << M(0, n-1) << endl;
    return 0;
}
```

Pseudo-code:
``` pseudo-code

function M(a, b)
    dp = matrix of size n x n, initialized to -1

    for i from n-1 down to 0
        for j from i to n-1

            if (i==j)
                dp[i][j] = 0;

            else
                dp[i][j] = infinity;
                for k from i to j-1
                    dp[i][j] = min(dp[i][j], dp[i][k]+dp[k+1][j]+p[i,k,j]);

    return dp[1][n];
```
